Board Game Piece Rules
General Notes
Each piece has its own movement, special ability, and capture method.
Some pieces can move and then use an ability, while others must choose between moving or capturing. If a piece triggers a trap while moving, it is captured immediately and stops on the trap space, even if that was not its final destination.

Pieces
1. Horizontal Diagonal
Abbreviation: HD
Capture Method: A, B, or C
Movement
The Horizontal Diagonal piece can move horizontally by 1 block.
Capture
This piece can capture diagonally up to 2 blocks away without moving onto the captured space.
It can capture in all four diagonal directions at the same time.
Turn Rules
This piece cannot capture and then move.
It may either:
Move first, then capture
Capture without moving

2. Trap Maker
Capture Method: A
Movement
The Trap Maker can move 1 block in any of the 8 directions.
Special Ability: Create Trap
The Trap Maker can place a trap either:
Under itself
On the space it started from this round
Trap Rules
Once a trap is placed, the player may trigger any number of their traps whenever they want.
A trap can also be triggered if an opponent captures the space where the trap is located.

3. Standard
Capture Method: B or C
Movement
The Standard piece can move horizontally up to 2 blocks per round.
It may turn during the movement, allowing it to move in an L-shape.
Capture
The Standard piece can capture any space it has walked over during its movement.
Trap Rule
If the Standard piece walks over a trap and that trap is triggered, the piece is captured immediately and stops on that trap space, even if its final destination was somewhere else.

4. Detector
Capture Method: D
Movement
The Detector can move 1 block in any direction.
Special Ability: Detect
The Detector can toss out up to 3 detection markers.
Each detection marker expands horizontally from the space where it lands.
Detection markers can only be tossed to spaces within 1 block of the Detector.
Detection Rules
When a detection marker is used, the opponent must say whether there are any pieces or traps in the detected area.
The opponent must give the exact locations of anything found.
However, the opponent does not have to say whether each object is a piece or a trap.
Turn Rules
The Detector may:
Detect, then move
Move, then detect
Detect without moving

5. Long Range
Capture Method: B
Movement
The Long Range piece can move horizontally.
Capture
The Long Range piece can capture spaces that are either 2 or 3 blocks away in the four horizontal directions.
This means it can capture up to 8 different spaces.
Turn Rules
The Long Range piece must choose between moving or capturing.
It cannot:
Move and then capture
Capture and then move
It must either:
Move without capturing
Capture without moving

6. Pusher
Capture Method: E
Movement
The Pusher can move horizontally by 1 block.
Special Ability: Push
The Pusher can toss out up to 2 push markers.
Each push marker pushes pieces away from the center by 1 block.
Push markers can be tossed to any of the 8 spaces around the Pusher.
Turn Rules
The Pusher may:
Move, then toss push markers
Toss push markers without moving
The Pusher cannot toss push markers and then move.

7. Dragger
Capture Method: F
Movement
The Dragger can move horizontally by 1 block.
Capture
The Dragger can capture spaces in a knight-shape around it, giving it 8 possible capture spots.
Special Ability: Drag
The Dragger can toss out up to 3 drag markers.
When a piece is dragged, the owner of that piece does not have to reveal the original location of the dragged piece.
Turn Rules
The Dragger cannot capture and then move.
It may either:
Move first, then capture
Capture without moving

8. Road Maker
Movement
The Road Maker moves like a Trap Maker.
It can move 1 block in any of the 8 directions.
Special Ability: Build Roads
The Road Maker can build road spaces.
If a piece is on one road space, it can move to any other road space.
The road spaces do not need to be connected.
Road Rule
A piece cannot capture after moving through the road.
Exception: Trap Makers can still capture or use their function after moving through a road.
Function
The Road Maker functions like a Trap Maker.

